<article id="post-1172" class="post-1172 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-costa-rica category-general tag-christmas">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/12/the-christmas-season-in-costa-rica/" rel="bookmark">The Christmas season in Costa Rica</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>It&#8217;s now December. Any of you who have been following my Twitter feed know that Costa Rica not only started preparing for Christmas back in September, but that I&#8217;ve had a few problems comprehending that it&#8217;s actually the Christmas season now. (The &#8220;Christmas season&#8221;, at least as I define it, is the month of December. No earlier, no later.)<br />
I&#8217;m having trouble comprehending this for one simple reason: I&#8217;m still wearing shorts and sandals.  <br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/12/the-christmas-season-in-costa-rica/#more-1172" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;The Christmas season in Costa Rica&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/12/the-christmas-season-in-costa-rica/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2008-12-06T11:06:30-07:00">6 December 2008</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/costa-rica/" rel="category tag">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/christmas/" rel="tag">christmas</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/12/the-christmas-season-in-costa-rica/#comments">2 Comments<span class="screen-reader-text"> on The Christmas season in Costa Rica</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
</article><!-- #post-1172 -->

<article id="post-1113" class="post-1113 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-costa-rica category-general category-rants tag-christmas">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/09/actually-make-that-18-things/" rel="bookmark">Actually, make that 18 things</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Last week, barely hours after Independence Day here was over, the stores started switching over their wares from Mother&#8217;s Day (in August) to &#8230; Christmas decorations.  <br />
Santa Claus is already in the aisles. This is so not fair. It&#8217;s the middle of freaking <em>September</em>, people!!<br />
Fortunately, they haven&#8217;t started playing Christmas music. I think I&#8217;d have to kill myself if they did. Ugh.</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/09/actually-make-that-18-things/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2008-09-23T21:17:41-06:00">23 September 2008</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/costa-rica/" rel="category tag">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/rants/" rel="category tag">Rants</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/christmas/" rel="tag">christmas</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/09/actually-make-that-18-things/#comments">6 Comments<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Actually, make that 18 things</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
</article><!-- #post-1113 -->

<article id="post-880" class="post-880 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general tag-christmas">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/christmas-in-calgary-2007/" rel="bookmark">Christmas in Calgary 2007</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Another Christmas has come and is now waning. It&#8217;s been a long, but good day. Our child isn&#8217;t old enough yet to truly understand Christmas (although the morning nap appeared to be aborted due to the desire to be around all the unwrapping of presents), but that doesn&#8217;t mean Mom and Dad aren&#8217;t keen.<br />
I think we were more interested in our baby&#8217;s presents than in our own.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/christmas-in-calgary-2007/#more-880" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Christmas in Calgary 2007&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/christmas-in-calgary-2007/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2007-12-25T21:46:54-07:00">25 December 2007</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/christmas/" rel="tag">christmas</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/christmas-in-calgary-2007/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Christmas in Calgary 2007</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
</article><!-- #post-880 -->

<article id="post-879" class="post-879 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-children category-general tag-christmas">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/father-christmas/" rel="bookmark">Father Christmas</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>A bit of a realisation hit me today: this is the fifth Christmas since my father passed away. Five years of listening to <em>Christmas at King&#8217;s College</em>&#8216;s version of <em>Hark! The Herald Angels Sing</em> and <em>God Rest Ye Merry Gentlemen</em> without also hearing my father singing along.<br />
Well, at least outside of my own memory, that is.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/father-christmas/#more-879" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Father Christmas&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/father-christmas/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2007-12-25T14:49:32-07:00">25 December 2007</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/children/" rel="category tag">Children</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/christmas/" rel="tag">christmas</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/12/father-christmas/#comments">1 Comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Father Christmas</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
</article><!-- #post-879 -->

<article id="post-480" class="post-480 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-travel tag-calgary tag-christmas tag-new-years-eve tag-oakville tag-ontario">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/12/christmas-in-oakville-with-chris-and-kaz-new-years-with-alex/" rel="bookmark">Christmas in Oakville with Chris and Kaz, New Years with Alex</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>I had hoped to go some place warm for the Christmas holidays this year. I wanted to put Christmas lights on a palm tree. I wanted to make sandmen. I wanted nothing more to worry about than getting a sunburn on Boxing day.<br />
So naturally, I ended up arriving at Pearson International Airport at 6:30 on the morning of 23 December, catching the end of a nasty two-day snowstorm. There&#8217;s poetic justice in this, somewhere.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/12/christmas-in-oakville-with-chris-and-kaz-new-years-with-alex/#more-480" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Christmas in Oakville with Chris and Kaz, New Years with Alex&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/12/christmas-in-oakville-with-chris-and-kaz-new-years-with-alex/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2004-12-31T21:15:20-07:00">31 December 2004</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/travel/" rel="category tag">Travel</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/calgary/" rel="tag">calgary</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/christmas/" rel="tag">christmas</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/new-years-eve/" rel="tag">new years eve</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/oakville/" rel="tag">oakville</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/ontario/" rel="tag">ontario</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/12/christmas-in-oakville-with-chris-and-kaz-new-years-with-alex/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Christmas in Oakville with Chris and Kaz, New Years with Alex</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
